  "description": "Traditional tempering and slow simmering deepen the flavor so the meal tastes complete even with minimal oil. Bitter Gourd Pitlai with Little Millet brings a distinct structure, seasoning pattern, and grain-legume balance to the table.",
  "preparation": "",
  "cooking_steps": [
    "Simmer the vegetable in tamarind water and 300 ml fresh water over medium heat for 10 minutes until tender.",
    "Add the cooked toor dal, cooked pulse accent, ground spice paste, and salt. Cook on low heat for 8 minutes until the gravy thickens and the raw roast aroma disappears.",
    "Temper mustard and curry leaves in oil and pour into the pot.",
    "Rest 5 minutes before serving over the grain."
  ],
